The template applies, since there are Indonesian naming conventions wherein there is only a singular word that could stand for a complete name (without the western equivalent of a surname), and there is another Indonesian naming convention with affixations directly linking the person to one's parents, usually using a patrilinieal naming system. Thus, this is to give clarification that her name follows the western naming conventions, more specifically through her British-Australian father.
